@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

 INTRODUCTION


 Delfina's DSP56002 processor features a PLL (phase-locked loop) clock
 oscillator which allows the processor to operate at a high internal clock
 frequency using low frequency clock input.

 DelfTweak overclocks Delfina's DSP56002 by changing the multiplication factor
 which is used for determining DSP's internal clock frequency.

 The clock frequency of a standard Delfina Lite soundcard can be set as high
 as 16.4 GHz with DelfTweak! However, the reliable operation is achieved with
 a clock speed between 4-64 MHz (60% overclocking) only.
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"

 FEATURES


 ∑ capable of changing Delfina Lite's internal clock speed
 ∑ displays external and internal clock frequences and DSP frequency ratio
 ∑ supports any external clock (crystal) frequence in addition to standard 
   4 MHz external clock
 ∑ available frequency range with standard Delfina Lite: 4 MHz - 16.4 GHz!
@endnode

